{"id":18148,"title":"Utility of antimicrobial susceptibility testing of multiple Haemophilus influenzae isolates from throat swabs of children with adenoid hypertrophy.","abstract":"Eleven out of 40 children with adenoiditis were colonized with multiple genotypes of Haemophilus influenzae. Heterogeneous antibiotic susceptibility to ampicillin and cotrimoxazole was observed in 6 children. A multiple-colony methodology may potentially help to find the resistant strains of H. influenzae in patients who do not respond to the antibiotic treatment. ","date":"2014-06-13","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24815933","annotations":[{"name":"Antibacterial","weight":0.832107,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibacterial"},{"name":"Antibiotic resistance","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antibiotic_resistance"},{"name":"Antimicrobial","weight":0.778288,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antimicrobial"},{"name":"Haemophilus influenzae","weight":0.715955,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haemophilus_influenzae"},{"name":"Ampicillin","weight":0.627383,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ampicillin"},{"name":"Pharyngeal tonsil","weight":0.533107,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharyngeal_tonsil"},{"name":"Trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole","weight":0.458908,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trimethoprim/sulfamethoxazole"},{"name":"Genotype","weight":0.174442,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genotype"},{"name":"Haemophilus","weight":0.115795,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haemophilus"},{"name":"Strain (biology)","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strain_(biology)"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Hypertrophy","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"